[src:signal-estimation/cramér-rao-bound] Note, however, that if $1+b'(\theta )<1$ this bound might be less than the unbiased Cramér–Rao bound $1/I(\theta )$ .
[src:signal-estimation/cramér-rao-bound] For instance, in the example of estimating variance below, $1+b'(\theta )={\frac {n}{n+2}}<1$ .
