[src:signal-estimation/particle-filter-p01] In certain problems, the conditional distribution of observations, given the random states of the signal, may fail to have a density; the latter may be impossible or too complex to compute.
[src:signal-estimation/particle-filter-p01] In this situation, an additional level of approximation is necessitated.
